<HEAD>Newspaper: U.S. Attorney Probes Dinkins Stock</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 9 grafs to UPDATE with Dinkins' reax. Picks up 8th
graf pvs, `Inner City...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Federal prosecutors are investigating a controversial transaction through which Mayor-elect <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> said he transferred stock to his son, the Daily News reported Sunday. The probe by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Attorney <PERSON> Andrew </PERSON> <PERSON> Maloney </PERSON>'s office is part of a larger inquiry into a cable television franchise related to <ORGANIZATION> Inner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the News quoted unidentified law enforcement sources as saying. Investigators are trying to determine whether <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> transferred <LOCATION> Inner </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> stock to his son, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, through a genuine transaction in 1985; how much it was worth and whether taxes were fully paid, the News said. <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON>' spokesman, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Fishlow </PERSON>, said the mayor-elect had hired a criminal attorney, <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Stillman </PERSON>. `` I'm confident this inquiry will reveal that there's nothing with which I need to be concerned,'' <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> told reporters Sunday. `` Those of us in public life are subject to criticism and scrutiny of all sorts over time.'' <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> said the federal investigation is a response to a suggestion by his opponent, Republican <PERSON> Rudolph </PERSON> <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON>, that the stock deal be looked into. `` My marching order from Mr. <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON> is 1,000 percent cooperation,'' <PERSON> Stillman </PERSON> told the News. `` We want to put this thing to bed once and for all.'' <PERSON> Stillman </PERSON>, however, also described the investigation as `` <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Giuliani </PERSON>'s last hurrah.'' <PERSON> Dinkins </PERSON>, a Democrat, defeated