d potty chairs to make it easier for the little kids.'' So he made a toilet seat with an extra ring that could be pulled down to accommodate infants' smaller bottoms. Other people wanted one, so four years ago, he said, he sold the plumbing business to his son and started the three-employee toilet seat business. The double-ring seat has been marketed to hardware stores and children's furniture stores. The Ritzers say they have sold between 3,000 and 4,000 in the last 18 months.
