r to kill the constitutional reform legislation rather than let it pass with the referendum bill attached. Abandoning reforms would endanger peace negotiations with the April M19 Movement, the only one of <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION>'s five main guerrilla groups that has accepted an official peace plan. The legislation contains provisions for the guerrilla group to run candidates for <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. Its leader, <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Pizarro </PERSON>, has said the guerrillas would lay down their arms on Dec. 19, provided that the government passes the reform legislation.
